+feed({color: 'orange', date: 'July 5', title: '0x001: Programming'})
  | Video games were the inspiration for learning how to program and I think that's something shared by many programmers.
  |  Excited about making the next Final Fantasy or World of Warcraft, I took one of the #[+hl('"Computer Science 101"')] classes during my undergraduate studies.
  |  Oh man was that a let down!
  +nl(45)
  | The first programming course introduced C++ and I remember calling #[+codeHL('std::cout')] #[+hl('"kout"')] and #[+codeHL('std::cin')] #[+hl('"kin"')].
  |  Luckily I met Alex Wilson in the CS lab who helped me learn the C++ basics.
  |  I remember he introduced me to #[+codeHL('std::stringstream')] which would take any type and make it into a string (amazing stuff!).
  +nl(45)
  | Skipping a year, I took #[+hl('"Object Oriented Programming in Java"')] with Dr. Robert Schweller which turned out to be the most enjoyable class I ever took.
  |  Each course assignment was posed as a challenge to build a mini-game, implementing the new Java features we learned.
  |  I probably put 15 hours a day working on the final project (who cares about other classes when you're making a game!!).
  |  Unfortunately I didn't get to finish it in time, but it was definitely a fun project which taught me basics (of basics) in game development.
  +nl(45)

  +disqus('0x001')